    "attributes": {
        "action": "Remove permitted development rights for telegraph poles & require full planning",
        "additional_details": "Telecommunications operators can currently install telegraph poles for fibre broadband without applying for planning permission under existing permitted development rights.\r\n\r\nThis means Local Planning Authorities do not have to consult residents and operators are not required to consider alternatives such as underground cabling. Many residents only discover new poles when they appear in their street.",
        "background": "Remove permitted development rights for telegraph poles and require planning permission and resident consultation for all new installations.",
